# {{PROJECT_NAME}} - API Specification

> Version: 1.0.0
> Last Updated: {{CREATION_DATE}}
> Base URL: `http://localhost:3000/api/v1`

## Overview

This document defines the API structure, response formats, authentication mechanisms, and endpoint specifications for {{PROJECT_NAME}}.

## Authentication

### JWT Bearer Token

All protected endpoints require a JWT token in the Authorization header:

```
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

### Obtaining a Token

**Endpoint**: `POST /auth/login`

**Request**:
```json
{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}
```

**Response**:
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
    "user": {
      "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
      "email": "user@example.com",
      "name": "John Doe",
      "role": "user"
    }
  }
}
```

## Response Format

### Standard Success Response

All successful API responses follow this format:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {},
  "message": "Optional success message",
  "meta": {}
}
```

#### Fields

- `success` (boolean): Always `true` for successful responses
- `data` (object|array): The response payload
- `message` (string, optional): Human-readable success message
- `meta` (object, optional): Additional metadata (pagination, etc.)

### Standard Error Response

All error responses follow this format:

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "code": "ERROR_CODE",
    "message": "Human-readable error message",
    "details": []
  }
}
```

#### Fields

- `success` (boolean): Always `false` for errors
- `error.code` (string): Machine-readable error code
- `error.message` (string): Human-readable error description
- `error.details` (array, optional): Detailed error information (e.g., validation errors)

## Error Codes

| Code | HTTP Status | Description |
|------|-------------|-------------|
| `VALIDATION_ERROR` | 400 | Request validation failed |
| `UNAUTHORIZED` | 401 | Authentication required |
| `FORBIDDEN` | 403 | Insufficient permissions |
| `NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Resource not found |
| `CONFLICT` | 409 | Resource conflict (e.g., duplicate) |
| `INTERNAL_ERROR` | 500 | Internal server error |
| `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` | 503 | Service temporarily unavailable |

## Pagination

### Request Parameters

All list endpoints support pagination via query parameters:

- `page` (number, default: 1): Page number
- `limit` (number, default: 10, max: 100): Items per page

**Example**: `GET /api/v1/users?page=2&limit=20`

### Response Format

Paginated responses include a `meta` object:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": [],
  "meta": {
    "page": 2,
    "limit": 20,
    "total": 100,
    "totalPages": 5
  }
}
```

## Filtering and Sorting

### Filtering

Use query parameters for filtering:

**Example**: `GET /api/v1/users?role=admin&status=active`

### Sorting

Use `sort` parameter with field name (prefix with `-` for descending):

**Example**:
- `GET /api/v1/users?sort=name` (ascending)
- `GET /api/v1/users?sort=-createdAt` (descending)

## Field Selection

Use `fields` parameter to select specific fields (comma-separated):

**Example**: `GET /api/v1/users?fields=name,email,role`

## Common Headers

### Request Headers

| Header | Required | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| `Content-Type` | Yes (for POST/PUT) | `application/json` |
| `Authorization` | For protected routes | `Bearer <token>` |
| `Accept` | No | `application/json` (default) |

### Response Headers

| Header | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `Content-Type` | `application/json` |
| `X-RateLimit-Limit` | Rate limit maximum |
| `X-RateLimit-Remaining` | Rate limit remaining |
| `X-RateLimit-Reset` | Rate limit reset time |

## Rate Limiting

- **Window**: 15 minutes
- **Max Requests**: 100 requests per window per IP
- **Response**: 429 Too Many Requests when exceeded

**Error Response**:
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "code": "RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED",
    "message": "Too many requests, please try again later"
  }
}
```

## API Endpoints

### Authentication

#### Register User

**Endpoint**: `POST /api/v1/auth/register`

**Request**:
```json
{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "SecureP@ss123",
  "age": 25
}
```

**Response**: `201 Created`
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
    "user": {
      "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
      "name": "John Doe",
      "email": "john@example.com",
      "role": "user",
      "createdAt": "2024-01-15T10:30:00.000Z"
    }
  },
  "message": "User registered successfully"
}
```

**Validation Rules**:
- `name`: Required, 2-50 characters
- `email`: Required, valid email format
- `password`: Required, min 8 characters, must contain uppercase, lowercase, number
- `age`: Optional, must be >= 18

**Error Responses**:
- `400 VALIDATION_ERROR`: Invalid input
- `409 CONFLICT`: Email already exists

#### Login

**Endpoint**: `POST /api/v1/auth/login`

**Request**:
```json
{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "SecureP@ss123"
}
```

**Response**: `200 OK`
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
    "user": {
      "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
      "name": "John Doe",
      "email": "john@example.com",
      "role": "user"
    }
  }
}
```

**Error Responses**:
- `401 UNAUTHORIZED`: Invalid credentials

### Users

#### Get All Users

**Endpoint**: `GET /api/v1/users`

**Auth Required**: Yes (Admin only)

**Query Parameters**:
- `page` (number, default: 1)
- `limit` (number, default: 10)
- `role` (string, optional): Filter by role
- `search` (string, optional): Search by name or email
- `sort` (string, default: -createdAt)

**Example**: `GET /api/v1/users?page=1&limit=10&role=admin&sort=-createdAt`

**Response**: `200 OK`
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
      "name": "John Doe",
      "email": "john@example.com",
      "role": "user",
      "createdAt": "2024-01-15T10:30:00.000Z",
      "updatedAt": "2024-01-15T10:30:00.000Z"
    }
  ],
  "meta": {
    "page": 1,
    "limit": 10,
    "total": 50,
    "totalPages": 5
  }
}
```

#### Get User by ID

**Endpoint**: `GET /api/v1/users/:id`

**Auth Required**: Yes

**Path Parameters**:
- `id` (string): User ID

**Response**: `200 OK`
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "role": "user",
    "age": 25,
    "createdAt": "2024-01-15T10:30:00.000Z",
    "updatedAt": "2024-01-15T10:30:00.000Z"
  }
}
```

**Error Responses**:
- `404 NOT_FOUND`: User not found

#### Update User

**Endpoint**: `PUT /api/v1/users/:id`

**Auth Required**: Yes (Own profile or Admin)

**Path Parameters**:
- `id` (string): User ID

**Request**:
```json
{
  "name": "John Updated",
  "age": 26
}
```

**Response**: `200 OK`
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
    "name": "John Updated",
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "role": "user",
    "age": 26,
    "updatedAt": "2024-01-16T14:20:00.000Z"
  },
  "message": "User updated successfully"
}
```

**Validation Rules**:
- `name`: Optional, 2-50 characters if provided
- `age`: Optional, must be >= 18 if provided
- `email`: Cannot be updated via this endpoint

**Error Responses**:
- `403 FORBIDDEN`: Cannot update other user's profile
- `404 NOT_FOUND`: User not found

#### Delete User

**Endpoint**: `DELETE /api/v1/users/:id`

**Auth Required**: Yes (Admin only)

**Path Parameters**:
- `id` (string): User ID

**Response**: `200 OK`
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "User deleted successfully"
}
```

**Error Responses**:
- `403 FORBIDDEN`: Insufficient permissions
- `404 NOT_FOUND`: User not found

### Posts (Example Resource)

#### Create Post

**Endpoint**: `POST /api/v1/posts`

**Auth Required**: Yes

**Request**:
```json
{
  "title": "My First Post",
  "content": "This is the content of my first post.",
  "tags": ["tech", "javascript"],
  "published": true
}
```

**Response**: `201 Created`
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439012",
    "title": "My First Post",
    "content": "This is the content of my first post.",
    "tags": ["tech", "javascript"],
    "published": true,
    "author": {
      "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
      "name": "John Doe"
    },
    "createdAt": "2024-01-15T12:00:00.000Z",
    "updatedAt": "2024-01-15T12:00:00.000Z"
  },
  "message": "Post created successfully"
}
```

**Validation Rules**:
- `title`: Required, 3-100 characters
- `content`: Required, min 10 characters
- `tags`: Optional, array of strings
- `published`: Optional, boolean (default: false)

#### Get All Posts

**Endpoint**: `GET /api/v1/posts`

**Auth Required**: No

**Query Parameters**:
- `page` (number, default: 1)
- `limit` (number, default: 10)
- `author` (string, optional): Filter by author ID
- `tag` (string, optional): Filter by tag
- `published` (boolean, optional): Filter by published status
- `search` (string, optional): Search in title and content
- `sort` (string, default: -createdAt)

**Response**: `200 OK`
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439012",
      "title": "My First Post",
      "content": "This is the content...",
      "tags": ["tech", "javascript"],
      "published": true,
      "author": {
        "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
        "name": "John Doe"
      },
      "createdAt": "2024-01-15T12:00:00.000Z"
    }
  ],
  "meta": {
    "page": 1,
    "limit": 10,
    "total": 25,
    "totalPages": 3
  }
}
```

#### Get Post by ID

**Endpoint**: `GET /api/v1/posts/:id`

**Auth Required**: No (for published posts)

**Path Parameters**:
- `id` (string): Post ID

**Response**: `200 OK`
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439012",
    "title": "My First Post",
    "content": "This is the content of my first post.",
    "tags": ["tech", "javascript"],
    "published": true,
    "author": {
      "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
      "name": "John Doe",
      "email": "john@example.com"
    },
    "createdAt": "2024-01-15T12:00:00.000Z",
    "updatedAt": "2024-01-15T12:00:00.000Z"
  }
}
```

## Validation Error Format

When validation fails, the response includes detailed error information:

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
    "message": "Validation failed",
    "details": [
      {
        "field": "email",
        "message": "Invalid email format",
        "value": "invalid-email"
      },
      {
        "field": "password",
        "message": "Password must be at least 8 characters",
        "value": "short"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

## File Upload

### Upload Single File

**Endpoint**: `POST /api/v1/upload`

**Auth Required**: Yes

**Content-Type**: `multipart/form-data`

**Request**:
```
file: <binary data>
```

**Response**: `200 OK`
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "url": "https://cdn.example.com/uploads/abc123.jpg",
    "filename": "abc123.jpg",
    "size": 245678,
    "mimetype": "image/jpeg"
  }
}
```

**Limits**:
- Max file size: 5MB
- Allowed types: image/jpeg, image/png, image/gif

## Webhooks (if applicable)

### Webhook Format

All webhooks send POST requests with this format:

```json
{
  "event": "user.created",
  "timestamp": "2024-01-15T12:00:00.000Z",
  "data": {
    "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
    "email": "user@example.com"
  }
}
```

**Headers**:
- `X-Webhook-Signature`: HMAC-SHA256 signature for verification

